<div class="header">
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>Capital One (COF)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of Capital One Financial. Using actual fundamentals and derived assumptions.</p>
    <p class="date">Updated March 2026 · Data: StockAnalysis.com</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">{roundedIV !== null ? `$${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}` : 'N/A'}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of {currentPrice !== null ? `$${currentPrice.toFixed(2)}` : 'N/A'} {marginOfSafety !== null ? `(${marginOfSafety}%)` : ''}</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{revenueRow[0] !== undefined && revenueRow[0] !== null ? `$${(revenueRow[0] / 1000).toFixed(1)}B` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">TTM Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{startingCashFlow !== null ? `$${(startingCashFlow / 1000).toFixed(1)}B` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Base Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{epsRow[0] !== undefined && epsRow[0] !== null ? `$${epsRow[0].toFixed(2)}` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">EPS (Diluted)</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{sharesOutstanding !== null ? `${sharesOutstanding.toLocaleString()}M` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Shares Out.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{netCash !== null ? `$${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B` : 'N/A'}</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model to calculate the intrinsic value of Capital One.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Determine the Base Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>For financial institutions like COF, traditional Free Cash Flow can be skewed by core operational changes in loan issuance. However, we use the scraped Free Cash Flow of <strong>{startingCashFlow !== null ? `$${startingCashFlow.toLocaleString()}M` : 'N/A'}</strong> as the baseline for this model.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project Cash Flow for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We project cash flow growth at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}% per year</strong> for the next 5 years, derived from the recent historical Revenue CAGR to reflect near-term business momentum.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate Terminal Value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume growth stabilizes at a terminal rate of <strong>{(terminalGrowthRate * 100).toFixed(1)}% forever</strong>, representing mature long-term macroeconomic growth.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>Future cash flows are discounted back to today using a required rate of return (WACC) of <strong>{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</strong>, calculated via CAPM (Risk Free Rate + Beta × Equity Risk Premium).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate Equity Value Per Share</h4>
      <p>We add Net Cash ({netCash !== null ? `$${netCash.toLocaleString()}M` : 'N/A'}) to the Enterprise Value, then divide by the <strong>{sharesOutstanding !== null ? sharesOutstanding : 'N/A'} million</strong> outstanding shares to find intrinsic value per share.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>Derived Assumptions</h2>
  <p>The core drivers of this DCF model are mathematically derived from current fundamentals and explicit macro variables.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Derived from the 3-year historical revenue CAGR. Capped at logical bounds to prevent overextrapolation of near-term cycles in the financial sector.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Calculated using the Capital Asset Pricing Model (CAPM). Risk-free rate (10Y Treasury) = 4.18%, Beta = {derivedBeta}, Equity Risk Premium = 5.5%. Formula: 4.18% + ({derivedBeta} × 5.5%).
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(terminalGrowthRate * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        A long-term mature growth rate constrained by typical macroeconomic GDP growth and inflation expectations, specifically set to 2.5%.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

