  <!-- ═══ RISKS ═══ -->
  <h2>Risks & Limitations</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Credit Cycles:</strong> As a consumer lending institution, Capital One is highly sensitive to macroeconomic shifts, inflation, and loan default rates. A severe recession could materially reduce base cash flow.</li>
    <li><strong>Regulatory Changes:</strong> Financial institutions face strict capitalization requirements. Adjustments (e.g., Basel III endgame) could impact available free cash flow for equity holders.</li>
    <li><strong>Discover Acquisition:</strong> Pending merger or acquisition activities (like the proposed Discover Financial deal) can drastically alter both the capital structure and cash flow profile modeled here.</li>
  </ul>

